article_title: Obama Is 'In An Untenable Position' Over Obamacare (VIDEO)
article_text:
Obama blamed many of the delays on the "overwhelming" number of people who have visited the website, admitting that the website "hasn’t worked as smoothly as it was supposed to work."

"He's in an untenable position," Tapper said on CNN. "He wants to have people sign up, he gave out the 800 number, but at the same time there are serious problems and tens of millions of Americans who need to get on these exchanges because there is a Federal mandate that they sign up for insurance by next March, but are having trouble doing so."
